Date: Tue 2 Jun 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2015; 28(23) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=17831


American foulbrood of honey bees, Netherlands
---------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 June 2015 from Dr Christianne Bruschke, chief veterinary officer, Ministry of Economic Affairs, Ministry of Economic Affairs, The Hague, Netherlands

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 2 Jun 2015
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 2 Jun 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 29 May 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Paenibacillus larvae_
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (AVB 201-01): Berg en Terblijt, LIMBURG
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Jun 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 1 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0
Affected population: one hive had clinical signs of American foulbrood of honey bees
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 100 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comment: A 3 km [2 mi] perimeter has been established around the outbreak.
Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinarian Institute, Lelystad (national laboratory) / Bees/ pathogenic agent isolation on culture / 2 Jun 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In 2014, 4 outbreaks of American foulbrood were reported by the Netherlands. The outbreaks were located in the provinces of Drenthe (2) and Groningen (2). According to the final report: "All measures were lifted up for Stadskanaal. The event was closed as of 29 May 2015"; see report at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000017830_20150602_172231.pdf.

For additional information, please refer to the commentaries in the archived posts listed below. - Mod CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3405080,104.]
